    <h4 class="title">What are the symptoms of Parkinson's disease? How can symptoms be alleviated? </h4>
    <p class="subtitle">Parkinson’s disease
        disease (also known as Parkinson's disease) is a progressive damage to the nervous system that affects movement.
        Usually symptoms do not appear suddenly overnight, but slowly affect life. The symptoms may be different for
        each person. Another well-known chronic neurodegenerative disease is "Alzheimer's disease", but the symptoms of
        the two diseases are different at the beginning. Alzheimer's disease has more obvious cognitive deterioration at
        the beginning, while Parkinson's disease It is mainly characterized by uncoordinated body movements.
    </p>
